 “Handphone No.” is needed for the system to send SMS Notifications and OTP for login to

4.5 Contractor  [For EWR requestors ] 
*This is an optional feature*  
 Under Contractor, Users can save common contractor information for their night works.  
 Users can upload Contractor Data using a template or manually enter the Contractor Data.

Figure 17

The Contractor Data window will pop up.

to the TAMS system.

Figure 22  
 To edit a Main Task, click on the input fields for “Description ”, “Action By” and/or “Remarks” 
on the CEP Tasks Table to make changes. Check the box “Require MOC Monitoring” if require 
MOC support for the task.  
 To edit a Sub Task, click on the input fields for “Description”, “Action By”, “Start(HH:mm)” and 
“Duration ( mins) and/or “Remarks” on the CEP Tasks Table to make changes. If there are any 
changes made to the Start and Duration, the TAMS system will recalculate the End timing and 
Main Task Start, End and Duration values.  
 To add a Main Task, click on the “Insert M ain Task” button to add a new Main Task Row below 
the selected task (if the selected task is a Sub Task, the Row will be insert below the last sub 
task of the Main Task group).  
 To add a Sub Task, click on the “Insert Sub Task” button to add a new Sub Task Row below the 
selected Main T ask. 
 To delete a task, click on the radio button next to the Task No. and click on the “Delete Task” 
button.  
 The User can create a name for the CEP Template to help differentiate CEP Templates from 
each other. To provide/ change the name for the CEP Template, click on the input field next to 
“CEP Template Name” to make changes.  
 The User can choose to disable a CEP template, such that the CEP template cannot be seen in 
the EWR creation screen. To enable/disable a CEP Templat e, click on the drop down menu 
next to “Status” to make changes. To enable, select “Active”. To disable, select “Inactive”  
 Once the User is satisfied with their changes to CEP Tasks Table, click on the “Save” button to 
confirm changes.  
 From the CEP Template edit page, click “Return” button to return to the CEP Template Table 
page.

1 Track Access Manager  – Workspace Functions  
For Track Access Managers, the default homepage is the STAA page. In addition, the homepage has 
hyperlinks for easy access to other functions (numbered 1 – 5) 
 
Figure 1 
1) System Map. This is elaborated in  part 3, page  9. 
2) System Layout. This is elaborated in part 4, page 1111 
3) Emergency Request. This function is not available yet. The user guide will be updated when 
the feature is available  
4) Late Request. This is elaborated in part 6, page 14 
5) EWR Request Summary. This is elaborated in part 7, page 21 
 
2 STAA  
2.1 STAA Tab 
Columns TAM Approval, TAC Granting Time, SM Ack Time are intentionally left blank. The features 
are not available yet. This user guide will be updated when the features are avai lable.   
By default, STAA shows all allocated  AGATs  to be executed fo r the upcoming engineering hour, and 
also display AGATs that are of status Cancelled and Cancel Pending Approval  
OCC S/N is a running number and generated in the order : 
1) NSL 
a. NB – from MSO ( EOT) to JUR  
b. SB – from MSO (EOT) to JUR  
c. NS – MSO (EOT) to JUR  
2) EWL  
a. EB – TLO(EOT) to PSO (EOT)  
b. CE – XPO to CGO (EOT)  
c. WB – TLO (EOT) to PSO (EOT)  
d. CW – XPO to CGO (COT)  
e. EW – TLO (EOT) to PSO (EOT)  
f. CA – XPO to CGO (EOT)  
OCC number will not be re -used on the same  night.

AGAT pending TAC to grant track access will be on top with green highlight .

Only stations with AGAT will displayed. Station without  AGAT  will not be displayed.  
PIC ride-on PM will not be displayed  on its own . It will show under “Ride on PIC” column. User can 
click on the column to view the PICs that are ride -on PM.  
Interchange stations will appear in STAA under  both NS and EW line  the selected line by the

upcoming night’s works  (including C ancelled  and Cancel Pending Approval  AGAT) . Refer  to

 TAM can use the search options to search for more specific records. After selecting the 
options, click  Search  butto n.

 If there are a large number of entries in any summary or search table, number of entries per 
page can be adjusted with a drop down menu at the top/bottom of the summary table.  
 To change page numb er, click on the arrows at the top/bottom of the summary table to move 
forward or backwards in page.  
 To navigate to the exact page, click on the page number at the top/bottom of the summary 
table.

 To view more information, scroll the horizontal scrollbar.  
 To view individual AGAT, click the AGAT number.  To view PIC under PM, click on the number 
under the column Ride on PIC.

1 Track Access Controller  – Workspace Functions  
For Track Access Controllers , the default homepage is the STAA page. In addition, the homepage has 
hyperlinks for easy access to other functions (numbered 1 – 5) 
 
Figure 1 
1) System Map. This is elaborated in  part 2.3, page  8. 
2) System Layout. This is elaborated in part 4, page 11 
3) Emergency Request. This function is not available yet. The user guide will be updated when 
the fea ture is available  
4) Late Request . This is elaborated in part 6, page 13 
5) EWR Request Summary. This is elaborated in part 7, page 16 
 
2 STAA  
2.1 STAA Tab 
Columns TAM Approval, TAC Granting Time, SM Ack Time are intentionally left blank. The features 
are not available yet. This user guide will be updated when the features are available.   
By default, STAA shows all allocated  AGATs to be executed for the upcoming engineering hour, and 
also display AGATs that are of status Cancelled and Cancel Pending Approval  
OCC S/N is a running number and generated in the order : 
1) NSL 
a. NB – from MSO (EOT) to JUR  
b. SB – from MSO (EOT) to JUR  
c. NS – MSO (EOT) to JUR  
2) EWL  
a. EB – TLO(EOT) to PSO (EOT)  
b. CE – XPO to CGO (EOT)  
c. WB – TLO (EOT) to PSO (EOT)  
d. CW – XPO to CGO (COT)  
e. EW – TLO (EOT) to PSO (EOT)  
f. CA – XPO to CGO (EOT)  
OCC number will not be re -used on the same night.

1 PM/PIC Certification  
 The PM/PIC Certification function contains the records for certified PM/PICs for NSEWL, CCL 
& Depot.  
 The PM/PIC Certification function pulls training records with the SMRT ACE system to maintain 
an up to date list of PM/PICs.  
 Users can use the function to check on the validity of any PM/PICs certification, and PM/PIC 
Users can check their qualification expiry  or their currency fulfillment.  
 
Figure 1 
 To go to the PM/PIC Certification page, on the top menu bar, select PM/PIC Certification >> 
Enquiry . 
 
 
Figure 2 
 The user can adjust their search with the search options:  
1) Employee ID/NRIC/FIN  
2) PM/PIC Name  
3) SMRT/External Staff  
4) Course Certified  
5) Line Certified  6) Role  
7) Expiry Date of Certification  
8) Certified Date  
9) PM/PIC Currency  
10) PM/PIC Status  
 To show all PM/PIC records, click "Search" button right under the "PM/PIC Certification > 
Enquiry" title.  
 Click the Reset button to clear all the search options selected.

Title: TAMS User Guide – Viewer  Page 5 of 13

1) Employee ID (for SMRT staff) or NRIC/FIN (for external staff)  
2) PM/PIC Name  
3) PM/PIC Status  
4) Role – PM or PIC ( Note that PM and PI C certifications are listed as separate entries)  
5) SMRT or External Staff  
6) Expiry Date  
7) Line  
8) Course – Course code. This code is set by SMRTi.  
9) Certified Date  
10) History – Number of track access completed (this feature is not available yet)  
11) Currency – Period of currency, no. of access to track (this feature is not available yet)  
12) Status – Effective Date, Active/Inactive  
13) Remark

followings.  
 
For routing  with re-orientation  point , there will be a part of the route which the consist will repeat pass through  but travelling in opposite direction.  So, 
it is called as the overlap route.  
 
For the overlap route, user can  highlight  it in pink color which represents where the consist will repeat traveling in opposite direction 2 times. Example , 
starting from BSD RT 3, the consist is travelling in south direction and heading to the re -orientated point (i.e. BSH SB). But after re -orientated, for the 
same track, consist is travelling in north direction and heading to the end point (i.e. AMK). For each overlap route, it only allows consist travelling in 2 
times, if more than 2 times, it cannot be recorded in System.

       The group  has two columns: Employee ID/ NRIC/FIN and PM/PIC Name.  
 Certification Status & corresponding role  
The group  has two columns:  PM/PIC Status and Role.    PM/PIC Status is the overall status of this certification , i.e., Active or Inactive.  The status is  corresponding to his role as PM, PIC or PM(E) . 
 LTA/SMRT Staff & corresponding division and branch  
This group provides information to identify SMRT and LTA staff.   The first column SMRT/External indicates SMRT or LTA staff.   For SMRT staff, d ivision and branch are normally given.  If division and branch cells are  
empty, it means exception  occurs, i.e., this PM/PIC certification cannot associated with  an user account.

A number of rules apply to a qualified PM/PIC resource for TAMS : 
 Must have a valid PM/PIC certificate;   
 Must fulfil minimum C urrency  requirements;  
 Must have a valid TAMS user account;  
Any non -compliance to the above requirements will be disqualified as a PM/PIC.  
 
“PM/PIC Status” column indicate s Status Active represents a  valid PM/PIC. On the contrast, Status I nactive  stands for an  invalid PM/PIC.  
The following requirement s apply to a valid PM/PIC : 
a. Employment status is true  (means he or she is a staff)  
b. Certificate is not expir ed (Current date < Triennial expiry date )  
c. Fulfils Currency policy , i.e.,  4 times annually  (count in second retraining period)  
d. Alternatively, SMRTi and System admin istrator  can manually set it as Active (if applicable) in Edit Status Column
